  • Deprecated Classes 
    Class and Description
    org.deeplearning4j.spark.impl.common.repartition.AssignIndexFunction
    Use RDD.zipWithIndex() instead
    org.deeplearning4j.bagofwords.vectorizer.Builder

    Please use Collections.newSetFromMap(new ConcurrentHashMap<>())
    org.deeplearning4j.earlystopping.scorecalc.DataSetLossCalculatorCG
    Use DataSetLossCalculator instead for both MultiLayerNetwork and ComputationGraph
    org.deeplearning4j.models.glove.GloveWeightLookupTable
    org.deeplearning4j.nn.conf.layers.GravesBidirectionalLSTM
    use Bidirectional instead. With the Bidirectional layer wrapper you can make any recurrent layer bidirectional, in particular GravesLSTM. Note that this layer adds the output of both directions, which translates into "ADD" mode in Bidirectional. Usage: .layer(new Bidirectional(Bidirectional.Mode.ADD, new GravesLSTM.Builder()....build()))
    org.deeplearning4j.models.word2vec.wordstore.inmemory.InMemoryLookupCache
    org.deeplearning4j.spark.data.shuffle.IntPartitioner
    Use HashPartitioner instead
    org.deeplearning4j.optimize.api.IterationListener
    Use TrainingListener instead
    org.deeplearning4j.parallelism.MagicQueue
    org.deeplearning4j.zoo.ModelMetaData
    As of May 10, 2018. Will be removed in v1.1. Getters are now available on the inputShape from the ZooModel implementation.
    org.deeplearning4j.datasets.iterator.MultipleEpochsIterator
    Does not properly trigger the incrementing of epoch counts in MultiLayerNetwork/ComputationGraph. Use MultiLayerNetwork/ComputationGraph.fit(DataSetIterator, int numEpochs) instead
